properties.areaDesc: Coastal Waters From Point Grenville To Cape Shoalwater Out 10 Nm
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued March 2 at 8:54AM PST until March 4 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 25 kt and seas 8 to 11 feet at 16
seconds.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters From Point Grenville To Cape Shoalwater
Out 10 Nm.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 4 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher are expected to produce hazardous
wave conditions to small craft. Inexperienced mariners,
especially those operating smaller vessels should avoid
navigating in these conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 AM PST WEDNESDAY
